In England, in the seven days to 07 December, there were 287,119 new confirmed cases (507.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 November, there were 261,925 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 10% (25,194 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 12 December is 9,178,705 (16,231.1 cases per 100,000 population).
